	</script><BR><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><font class="h1font">Extended: Intermediate Decks</font></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr height="10"><td width="98%" bgcolor="#669933" height="10"><img src="/magic/gfx/trans.gif" width="6" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td><td valign="bottom" align="right"><img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/tg.gif" width="103" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td valign="top" align="right">
<img src="/magic/gfx/hrz/bg.gif" width="92" height="24" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td>
</tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Crimson Beatdown Bl/R v2.0</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont">Not Reviewed</font><font size=1>(13.00)</font> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=25185">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=4038">Joey "Wioslea" Haefele</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magic/main/mpage.php?member=4038&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I know it&#39;s only been a couple days since I put in v1.0, but I just traded a lot of my SW:CCG cards for some M:TG cards. I love this deck, and couldn&#39;t wait to put it up.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> August 22, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Creatures<br>
1 Cinder Shade<br>
1 Crimson Hellkite<br>
1 Crypt Angel<br>
1 Fire Elemental<br>
1 Flame Spirit<br>
1 Flowstone Crusher<br>
4 Ravenous Rats<br>
1 Viashino Cutthroat<br>
1 Lotus Guardian (artifact)<br>
<br>
Artifacts<br>
1 Bloodstone Cameo<br>
1 Planar Portal<br>
<br>
Sorcery<br>
2 Breath of Darigaaz<br>
3 Disintegrate<br>
3 Fireball<br>
4 Plague Spores<br>
4 Soul Burn<br>
<br>
Instants<br>
3 Agonizing Demise<br>
4 Howl from Beyond<br>
2 Incinerate<br>
1 Terminate<br>
1 Thunderbolt<br>
1 Urza&#39;s Rage<br>
<br>
Lands<br>
12 Mountain<br>
9 Swamp<br>
1 Urborg Volcano<br>
<br>
Sideboard<br>
1 Downhill Charge<br>
3 Firescreamer<br>
1 Lava Storm<br>
4 Phyrexian Reaper<br>
4 Phyrexian Slayer<br>
1 Spitting Earth<br>
1 Tsabo&#39;s Decree   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck is EXTREMELY fun to play. There&#39;s nothing like burning your opponent to death!<br>
<br>
The strategy is fairly simple. Just use the spells to destroy your opponent. All of the spells can also be used to destroy a pesky creature.<br>
<br>
If needed, due to the fact that your opponent has a lot of counter spells, the creatures then come into play. The rats will try to keep those counter spells out of your opponent&#39;s hand. And the rest of the creatures are extremely strong, and will maul your opponent, and his creatures.<br>
<br>
This deck wins LOTS of matches. There are a couple changes I want to make. First, I want more Planar Portals. If I can find the one in my deck, that&#39;s great, but I need more than one, if I want to find it every game. (Luckily, it&#39;s not needed to win most of the time.) Second, I want more Urza&#39;s Rages. 3 or 4 of them will do nicely in this deck. Unfortunately, I don&#39;t have $35 to buy 3 more. With my limited budget, I might be able to afford 1 more. I could have bought one, but I decided to spend 50 cents to buy 2 Fireballs, and 2 Disintegrates instead. (I saved over $10, just to have spells that CAN be countered.)<br>
<br>
With all of the spells in the deck, it&#39;s almost impossible to counter them all. Usually, my opponent wastes his counters saving his creatures, then BAM, I hit him with a 15 damage Fireball. Next turn, BAM, 15 damage Disintegrate, you&#39;re dead.<br>
<br>
Ok, sure, getting that many lands out is pretty tough. (I&#39;ve done it plenty of times, though.) But even 5 damage with a Fireball is plenty. A couple Fireballs, a couple Incinerates, a Thunderbolt, and some damage from creatures would be plenty of damage against the opponent.<br>
<br>
This deck is hard to beat. It can easily win a local tournament. It&#39;s not going to win any Regional Championships or anything. (That&#39;s why it&#39;s not listed as an Advanced Deck.) But I&#39;m sure the deck wouldn&#39;t come close to last. It would probably end up some where in the middle of the field. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/magic/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/magic/decks/decks.php?reviews=25185"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25185" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/magic/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font><BR></td></tr></table> <!-- #EndEditable --></td>
